				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">In a game with 3 save slots, have 4 actual slots in SRAM and a table of 3 indicies for the visible save slots. When saving, find the one unused actual slot, save there, then change the index in the table. The key is to use an atomic operation when changing data, which either succeeds or fails without changing data. In this case, the visible data doesn't change until the index is updated at the end.
<br />
<br />One problem with this is that the table of indicies is open to corruption. You could have the actual slots marked as valid/invalid to allow "recovery" of slots if the index becomes corrupt, much like a filesystem does when the directory doesn't get updated properly.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

