			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">OK, you start out with an index with values 1, 2, 3 and internal save slots 1, 2, and 3 used, and 4 is unused. Player saves game to slot 3. Internally you save game to slot 4, then change the index to 1, 2, 4. Now internal slots 1, 2, and 4 are used, and 3 is unused.
<br />
<br />The key is that if power is removed before the index is updated, it is as if the save was never done. After the single byte in the index is changed from 3 to 4, the save is complete. This is the atomic part (atomic meaning indivisible, not exactly the definition the physicists follow anymore!).</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

